@trevor-m Please update the PR title, and add a test for the new op converter in pytorch/test_forward.py.

You can add a test for `with_indices` variant in the existing max pool2d test, see
 https://github.com/apache/incubator-tvm/blob/master/tests/python/frontend/pytorch/test_forward.py#L523

Well, a test for TensorCore fails.

`HoistIfThenElse` transforms

```
for (n.inner, 0, 2) {
  for (o.inner, 0, 2) {
    if ((((threadIdx.y*2) + n.inner) < 2)) {
      if ((((threadIdx.z*2) + o.inner) < 4)) {
        if ((threadIdx.y < 1)) {
          if ((threadIdx.z < 2)) {
            tvm_store_matrix_sync(Conv.wmma.accumulator, 16, 16, 16, ((n.inner*2) + o.inner), tvm_access_ptr(type_annotation(), Conv, (((((threadIdx.y*401408) + (n.inner*200704)) + (blockIdx.z*1024)) + (threadIdx.z*512)) + (o.inner*256)), 256, 2), 16, "row_major")
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

into

```
if ((((threadIdx.y*2) + n.inner) < 2)) {
  if ((threadIdx.y < 1)) {
    if ((threadIdx.z < 2)) {
      for (n.inner, 0, 2) {
        for (o.inner, 0, 2) {
          if ((((threadIdx.z*2) + o.inner) < 4)) {
            tvm_store_matrix_sync(Conv.wmma.accumulator, 16, 16, 16, ((n.inner*2) + o.inner), tvm_access_ptr(type_annotation(), Conv, (((((threadIdx.y*401408) + (n.inner*200704)) + (blockIdx.z*1024)) + (threadIdx.z*512)) + (o.inner*256)), 256, 2), 16, "row_major")
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

where the `if` containing `n.inner` is wrongly hoisted, seeming like a bug of `HoistIfThenElse`. I will try to dig it out.

If you take a look here
```
auto inter_type = op->type.is_int() ? Int(16) : UInt(16);
    value_int8 << CastFromTo(value_16.str(), op->value.type(), inter_type);
    os << CastFromTo(value_int8.str(), inter_type, op->type);
```

We need to convert to `uint16` and then cast to `uint8`. No direct conversion from `fp16` to `uint8`.

ref: https://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/cuda-math-api/group__CUDA__MATH____HALF__MISC.html#group__CUDA__MATH____HALF__MISC
